# EAS upload rules (read from the GIT ROOT in monorepos — the app-level
# .easignore in examples/push-test-app is not consulted there). When this
# file exists it REPLACES .gitignore for deciding what uploads to the EAS
# cloud builder, so it must re-state every exclusion that matters:
#  - secrets stay out (.env, .npmrc)
#  - heavy/derived dirs stay out (node_modules, dist, native build dirs)
# ...while deliberately ALLOWING two files .gitignore blocks, because the
# builder needs them: examples/push-test-app/google-services.json (Firebase
# client config) and the packed @asyncify-hq/react-native *.tgz (the
# package's dist/ is git-ignored, so a bare file:../../ dependency arrives
# empty — see examples/push-test-app/README.md).

# secrets — never upload
.env
.env.*
.npmrc

# heavy / derived
node_modules/
dist/
*.log
.expo/
web-build/
coverage/

# native project dirs (regenerated by prebuild on the builder)
examples/push-test-app/android/
examples/push-test-app/ios/

# not needed for builds
.git/
